extends layout.jade

block page
  -var current_page = 'Rules'

block contents
  div.container.panel.panel-default
    h1 Rules
    h2 Roster
    ul
      li Every player on your team must be within the ranks Silver 1 and Distinguished Master Guardian, and could not have been higher than Distinguished Master Guardian, at any point in the past.
      li You can add players until you have 7 players on your roster, then to add players you need to drop players.
      li If a player is dropped from your roster they cannot be readded.
    h2 Matches
    ul
      li The team captains are required to email LowRankedLeague@mail.com your teams name, each player on your teams Steam Profile link, and the Steam Group link.
      li If a game has been rescheduled, both team captains must email LowRankedLeague@mail.com with the new Date/Time in Pacific Standard Time (PST)
      li At the end of each match your team captain is required to download the games demo from popflash, and send it to LowRankedLeague@mail.com, for proof of scores, and game.
      li The team captain must check in 5-10 minutes prior to the match by emailing LowRankedLeague@mail.com with the subject "Checking In" with a link to the steam profiles of each player on their team that will be playing in that game.
      li If a team does not have 5 players able to play by the scheduled time of the game, it will be an automatic forfeit. Each team is allowed 7 players on the roster.
      li If two teams are unable to agree on a date/time for the games to be played, the preset scheduled time/date will be used.
      li In the chance both teams are unable to participate the game will result in a double forfeit.
      li Once a game has begun, it cannot be restarted, or stopped. (Except for Timeouts)
      li You may not use your own server, the server must be a Popflash Scrim server located as close to the Home Team's average states as possible, for example a team with most its players in lets say California, should either choose Las Vegas, Nevada, Dallas, Texas, or if an Los Angeles server is available that one. 
    h2 Behavior
    ul
      li Have good sportsmanship, and don't be disrespectful to your opponents.
      li If you suspect a player on the other team is cheating or is smurfing, send LowRankedLeague@mail.com an email with the games Demo, and the player that you think is cheating/smurfings name, and we'll do our best.
      li If a player is caught cheating (Via spectate, or ban from Popflash) it will result in an instant Game Disqualification, and your team will be required to find a replacement player, or drop from the league.
      li If a player continues to harass players on the enemy team, they can be temporarily suspended from the league for X games depending on how far they went. (Unlikely this happend) 
